    <string name="help_heatmap_title">What is the heatmap?</string>
    <string name="help_heatmap_body">The colored overlay shows where Mira looked when making its decision. Bright areas are regions Mira considered important. If the bright area lands on the cervix and matches what you see as acetowhite, the result is more trustworthy. If it lands on the speculum or somewhere else, treat the result with caution and consider re-imaging.</string>
    <string name="help_confidence_title">What does confidence mean?</string>
    <string name="help_confidence_body">Confidence is how sure Mira is about its answer, from 0 to 100%. Above 80% is strong. Below the threshold you set in Settings (default 65%), Mira will mark the result as inconclusive and ask you to re-image. Your clinical judgment matters more than the number.</string>
    <string name="result_confidence">Confidence: %1$d%%</string>
